{"parse":{"title":"Royal Academy of Dutch language and literature","pageid":40578272,"revid":784849144,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox vcard\" style=\"width:22em\"><caption class=\"fn org\">Royal Academy <br />of Dutch language and literature<br /><br /><a href=\"/wiki/Dutch_language\" title=\"Dutch language\">Dutch</a>: <i><span lang=\"nl\">Koninklijke Academie voor Nederlandse Taal- en Letterkunde<br /> (KANTL)</span></i></caption><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/File:Oombergen_001.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Oombergen 001.jpg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c4/Oombergen_001.jpg/150px-Oombergen_001.jpg\" width=\"150\" height=\"267\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c4/Oombergen_001.jpg/225px-Oombergen_001.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c4/Oombergen_001.jpg/300px-Oombergen_001.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"1080\" data-file-height=\"1920\" /></a><div><b>KANTL</b></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.6em;\">Formation</th><td class=\"note\">\n1886</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.6em;\">Headquarters</th><td>\n<i>Huis van Oombergen</i>, Koningsstraat 18 in <a href=\"/wiki/Ghent\" title=\"Ghent\">Ghent</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Belgium\" title=\"Belgium\">Belgium</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.6em;\"><div style=\"padding:0.1em 0;line-height:1.2em;\">voorzitter (president)</div></th><td>\nMarcel De Smedt</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\" style=\"padding-right:0.6em;\">Website</th><td>\n<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"http://www.kantl.be\">http://www.kantl.be</a></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Koninklijke Academie voor Nederlandse Taal- en Letterkunde</b>, otherwise known as the <b>KANTL</b>, is an Academy established to study and promote the <a href=\"/wiki/Dutch_language\" title=\"Dutch language\">Dutch language</a> in <a href=\"/wiki/Flanders\" title=\"Flanders\">Flanders</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Royal_Academy_of_Dutch_language_and_literature_Prize\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Royal Academy of Dutch language and literature Prize</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Prize_Winners_2003-2012\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Prize Winners 2003-2012</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Notes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Notes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Royal_Academy_of_Dutch_language_and_literature&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: History\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The Royal Academy of Dutch language and literature (abbreviated to KANTL) is a government organization which was established in 1886 by Royal Decree as <i><b>Koninklijke Vlaamse Academie voor Taal- en Letterkunde</b></i> (Royal Flemish Academy for language and literature).<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In 1972 the name of The Royal Flemish Academy for language and literature was changed to The Royal Academy of Dutch language and literature,<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> and in 1981 the existence of the Academy was confirmed by a decree of the Council for Cultural Affairs for the Dutch cultural community (the predecessor of the Flemish Parliament) (decree of 13 February 1980). The KANTL is now an institution of the Flemish Government.\n</p><p>The Academy was the first official institution of Belgium where the Dutch language was examined scientifically and to encourage coordination between scientific academic fields using the Dutch language. This ended in 1938 when the <a href=\"/wiki/Royal_Flemish_Academy_of_Belgium_for_Science_and_the_Arts\" title=\"Royal Flemish Academy of Belgium for Science and the Arts\">Royal Flemish Academy of Belgium for Science and the Arts</a> and the <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Royal_Academy_of_Medicine_of_Belgium&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Royal Academy of Medicine of Belgium (page does not exist)\">Royal Academy of Medicine of Belgium</a> were set up.  From this point on the Academy\u2019s power was limited to the Dutch language and its literature. To do this, it is still has an advisory function for the Flemish government. The Flemish Academy played an important role in Flemish emancipation and sent the Flemish Movement in a cultural and intellectual to a higher level. In political terms, however, the Academy is always neutral.\n</p><p>Since 1939 The Academy consists of 30 members and 25 foreign honorary Members.\n</p><p>The Royal Academy of Dutch language and literature is housed in the House of Oombergen in the Koningsstraat in Ghent. The building was restored in 2012.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Royal_Academy_of_Dutch_language_and_literature_Prize\">Royal Academy of Dutch language and literature Prize</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Royal_Academy_of_Dutch_language_and_literature&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Royal Academy of Dutch language and literature Prize\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Since its early days, the Royal Academy has issued an annual prize for what the Academy considered outstanding research and work in the Dutch language. However, since 2005 this has changed to a more general calling for those working in the field of Dutch language and literature. Thus a prize is offered for an essay, for a study on the old Dutch language, for literature, for poetry, for prose and for culture.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Prize_Winners_2003-2012\">Prize Winners 2003-2012</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Royal_Academy_of_Dutch_language_and_literature&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Prize Winners 2003-2012\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>2012 <a href=\"/wiki/Tom_Lanoye\" title=\"Tom Lanoye\">Tom Lanoye</a> (Writer)</li>\n<li>2011 <a href=\"/wiki/Arnon_Grunberg\" title=\"Arnon Grunberg\">Arnon Grunberg</a> (Writer)</li>\n<li>2010 <a href=\"/wiki/Leo_Vroman\" title=\"Leo Vroman\">Leo Vroman</a> (Poet)</li>\n<li>2009 Helmut Tervooren</li>\n<li>2008 <a href=\"/wiki/Stefan_Hertmans\" title=\"Stefan Hertmans\">Stefan Hertmans</a> (Writer)</li>\n<li>2007 <a href=\"/wiki/David_Van_Reybrouck\" title=\"David Van Reybrouck\">David Van Reybrouck</a></li>\n<li>2006 <a href=\"/wiki/Stefan_Brijs\" title=\"Stefan Brijs\">Stefan Brijs</a></li>\n<li>2005 <a href=\"https://nl.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gerrit_Kouwenaar\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"nl:Gerrit Kouwenaar\">Gerrit Kouwenaar</a> (Poet)</li>\n<li>2004 Peter Louis Seize</li>\n<li>2003 <a href=\"https://nl.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jan_de_Roder\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"nl:Jan de Roder\">Jan de Roder</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Royal_Academy_of_Dutch_language_and_literature&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Dutch_Language_Union\" title=\"Dutch Language Union\">Dutch Language Union</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Royal_Flemish_Academy_of_Belgium_for_Science_and_the_Arts\" title=\"Royal Flemish Academy of Belgium for Science and the Arts\">Royal Flemish Academy of Belgium for Science and the Arts</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Notes\">Notes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Royal_Academy_of_Dutch_language_and_literature&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: Notes\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Royal Decree from 8 July 1886</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Royal Decree from 20 April 1972</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Royal_Academy_of_Dutch_language_and_literature&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editse